<h2><a name="dt4dtd.xslt">dt4dtd.xslt</a></h2>
<p>
<b>Applies to:</b> source XDR file
</p>
<p>
The current <bib:ref name="XDR" />s for PROMPT datasources have been automatically
converted from <bib:ref name="DTD" />s using the <bib:ref name="DT4DTD" /> extension
(which allows to define datatypes in DTDs). <code>dt4dtd.xslt</code> takes an
XDR document with attribute definitions based on DT4DTD and converts them into
their proper XDR counterparts, making the XDR both more expressive (data types
actually can be validated) and readable.
</p>

